Then the sea, then the air, then the fire-laden ether itself, all are left unmixed with their clear bodies 5 and some are lighter than others, and clearest and lightest of all ether floats upon the airy currents, and blends not its clear body with the troubled airs 5 it suffers all these things below to be upset with furious hurricanes, suffers them to be troubled by wayward storms3 while it carries along its own fires gliding with a changeless onward sweep.
